## §4 — Create `scripts/` by hand (no extract, no fat `.md`)

From **project root** (folder that already has `backend/` after prompt-only rebuild or partial copy):

```bash
mkdir -p scripts
```

**`scripts/setup.sh`**

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail
ROOT="$(cd "$(dirname "$0")/.." && pwd)"
cd "$ROOT/backend"
python3 -m venv .venv
# shellcheck disable=SC1091
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install pytest httpx
echo "Backend ready. From backend/: source .venv/bin/activate && uvicorn app.main:app --reload"
```

**`scripts/ingest_docs.sh`**

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
# PHASE_1 — ingest data/knowledge → Chroma (needs OPENAI_API_KEY in .env)
set -euo pipefail
ROOT="$(cd "$(dirname "$0")/.." && pwd)"
cd "$ROOT/backend"
# shellcheck disable=SC1091
if [[ -f .venv/bin/activate ]]; then source .venv/bin/activate; fi
python -m app.cli_ingest
```

Then:

```bash
chmod +x scripts/setup.sh scripts/ingest_docs.sh
```

**Same thing without `.sh` files** (run yourself from project root):

```bash
cd backend && python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate && pip install -r requirements.txt && pip install pytest httpx
# after .env is set and data/knowledge has files:
cd backend && source .venv/bin/activate && python -m app.cli_ingest
```

